The paper deals with a data detector ASIC for massive multiuser MIMO wireless systems, which involves information theory (cs.IT), signal processing (cs.AR), control systems (cs.SY), networking and internet architecture (cs.NI), and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on achieving near-optimal error-rate performance and supporting 32 users transmitting 256-QAM simultaneously suggests a strong emphasis on information theory and signal processing, hence cs.IT and cs.AR are the most likely categories. The mention of soft-input soft-output capabilities for iterative detection and decoding suggests a possible connection to machine learning, hence cs.LG is also a likely category. The mention of realistic channel conditions and achieving high throughput with low power consumption suggests a possible connection to networking and internet architecture, hence cs.NI is a less likely but still possible category. Finally, the mention of achieving high SNR and improving on existing data detectors suggests a possible connection to control systems, hence cs.SY is also a less likely but still possible category.
